(59, 1, '2017-09-15 18:30:26', '2017-09-15 17:30:26', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Each year, over </span><b>6 million </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">people flock to Bavaria in Germany to celebrate </span><b>Oktoberfest. </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The festival lasts for 2 weeks and consists of drinking copious amounts of Beer, eating lots of salted pretzels and lots of German entertainment. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, </span><b>Oktoberfest</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> isn’t just celebrated in Germany, several people around the world host their own Oktoberfest themed parties. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Luckily for you, we’ve compiled 4 tips on how you can throw the ultimate Oktoberfest party:  </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1><b>#1: Decorate The Party Venue</b></h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Oktoberfest celebrations traditionally take place in large Beer tents in Germany, so if you would like your party to be truly authentic, consider hiring a beer tent! Alternatively, you could host the party indoors and still enjoy those authentic Oktoberfest vibes!</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Either way, you’ll need to liven up the venue with some Oktoberfest themed decorations. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Start off by hanging up some bunting. Remember, the Bavarian colours are blue and white, so our </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Flag-And-Pennant-Bunting/Oktoberfest-Bunting\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">chequered bunting</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is sure to do the trick. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Top tip:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> To add a fun twist to your decor, throw in a few </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Male-Birthday-Balloons/Beer-Mug-Supershape-Balloon\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Beer-shaped helium balloons</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">!</span>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-61\" src=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/beer.png\" alt=\"Oktoberfest beer\" width=\"450\" height=\"533\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You could also get some blue and white balloons, and place them around the room to keep in line with the Oktoberfest colour theme. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1><b>#2: Set Up A Buffet Table </b></h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Next, you’ll want to set up your buffet table, with a range of delicious authentic German foods. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Top tip: </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">It goes without saying that you will make, or purchase some German styled salted pretzels, but why not make some beer-braised hot dogs topped with sauerkraut? </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To make them, simply simmer the sauerkraut in a pot with half a cup of dark beer, for 5 minutes and season to taste. Then top your hot dogs with the beer braised sauerkraut and add a squirt of mustard! </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">With all these finger foods, be sure to stock up on </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Caribbean-Blue-Tableware/Caribbean-Blue-2ply-Dinner-Napkins-x20\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">napkins</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">!</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1><b>#3: Oktoberfest Entertainment</b></h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Once your party is in full swing, don’t forget to capture the moment with some memorable snaps!</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Top tip: set up a photobooth!</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">We’ve got two awesome photo ideas:</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Set up this </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Scene-Setter-Photo-Prop/Double-Sided-Oktoberfest-Photo-Prop\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">backdrop</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and take photos of your friends standing behind it with their faces peering through.</span></li>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Take a group photo with all of your friends holding one of these</span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Party-Photo-Props/Oktoberfest-Party-Photo-Props\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Oktoberfest themed props</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-62\" src=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/props-1.png\" alt=\"Oktoberfest backdrop\" width=\"496\" height=\"486\" /><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-63\" src=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/props-2.png\" alt=\"Oktoberfest props\" width=\"473\" height=\"522\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also be sure to include lots of traditional songs that are played at Oktoberfest to your playlist! </span>\r\n<h1><b>#4: Dress Up </b></h1>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Insist that your guests arrive in fancy dress! For the ladies, the classic </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Around-The-World-Costumes/Oktoberfest-Female-Fancy-Dress-Costumes\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dirndl dress </span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">with the bodice, low cut puffy sleeves, long skirt and an apron will be perfect for the ladies - for the gentlemen a </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Around-The-World-Costumes/Oktoberfest-Male-Fancy-Dress-Costumes\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Bavarian suit inspired costume </span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">will do just the trick. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Top tip:</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> For the ladies pair your Dirndl dresses with some tights and a pair of heels - also remember to tie your Dirndl on the correct side - if you tie it to the left, it signals that you are single and ready to mingle, and if you tie it to the right shows you are already taken!</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For the gents, add a feather or a German pewter pin to your hat to finish off your look. </span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">So here we have it folks - 4 tips on how to throw the ultimate Oktoberfest party!</span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Be sure to follow us on Twitter </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/gointuk\">@gointuk</a> for business tips and party ideas! </span>', '4 Tips On How To Throw The ULTIMATE Oktoberfest Party!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '4-tips-on-how-to-throw-the-ultimate-oktoberfest-party', '', '', '2018-11-14 08:17:25', '2018-11-14 08:17:25', '', 0, 'https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/?p=59', 0, 'post', '', 0),
