(212, 1, '2018-02-12 16:46:07', '2018-02-12 16:46:07', '<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-211\" src=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/cocktails.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"584\" height=\"389\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You have the menu for your reception all set, </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Wedding-Decorations?zenid=24g9e9kgllpa06urqatr4kt916\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">you have picked out the perfect wedding decorations and wedding accessories</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. You\'ve finished the seating chart and finalized the wedding present list. </span><b>Now it is time to turn your attention to another crucial element of the majority of wedding receptions; the drinks. </b>\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Rise of the Signature Wedding Cocktail</span></h1>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">One idea that is growing in popularity, and for good reason,</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is the signature wedding cocktail. </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You can pick one that matches your decor scheme, your personality, your venue or</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> just downright tastes delicious. </span></i>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There is a potential bonus in the idea for the budget conscious as well as rather than forking over for a full open bar you could simply</span><b> opt to offer soda, beer and wine and then as a bonus, your stunning signature drink</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Serve it all in the </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Wedding-Decorations?zenid=24g9e9kgllpa06urqatr4kt916\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">appropriate wedding glassware</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and it should all go down very well. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Open up any bartender\'s companion book and you will find that there are </span><b>hundreds of great cocktail \'recipes\' </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">out there and the very adventurous could even consider creating their own. To provide you with a little inspiration though these are some of our favorite choices. </span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ciroc Lola </span></h2>\r\n<b>Flowers are a big part of any wedding</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and so the fact that not only does this cocktail contain a rather flowery element but is also customarily garnished with a flower means it will fit right in. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Its light pleasant taste should make it universally popular as well. </span></i>\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients</b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1-ounce Cîroc Vodka</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 1/2 ounces pomegranate juice</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 teaspoon elderflower liqueur</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 splash champagne</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 food grade flower </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Combine all of the ingredients, with the exception of the champagne</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, together in a cocktail shaker. Shake, pour over ice the glass and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">top of with champagne and your beautiful bloom. </span></i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cranberry Kiss </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This dark pink concoction is both </span><b>sweet-tart and spicy</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and provides as much of a </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">visual spark as it does a kick to the tastebuds. </span></i>\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients</b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">3/4 ounces Spiced Rum</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 ounces collins mix</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 ounces cranberry juice</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lemon or lime wedge (according to personal taste) </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Combine all ingredients in a cocktail shaker,</span><b> stir and serve over ice</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> adding a lemon or lime wedge for garnish. The green of the lime against the cranberry colored cocktail does offer the biggest visual impact </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">but may not be to everyone\'s taste. </span></i>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cuervo Especial Oasis</span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Perfect for the university sweethearts who originally bonded over shots of tequila,</span><b> this grown-up take on the ever-popular white spirit is a sophisticated stunner. </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Ingredients</b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 ounce Cuervo Especial Gold</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1/2 ounces triple sec</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">2 ounces cranberry juice</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1-ounce orange juice</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">1 slice lemon, for garnish </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Combine all ingredients in a cocktail shaker</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, serve in a martini glass garnished with lemon. </span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The Craft Beer Option </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not sure that all of your guests will be persuaded to </span><b>trade a cold beer for a cocktail?</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Then why not consider the craft beer option instead, </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">served in appropriately personalized bottles of course</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Those feeling ambitious and crafty could consider brewing their own or you can</span><b> tap the local brewpub instead. </b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'The Signature Cocktail - One More Way to Make Your Wedding All Your Own', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '210-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-02-12 16:46:07', '2018-02-12 16:46:07', '', 210, 'https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/2018/02/12/210-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(213, 1, '2018-02-28 16:48:24', '2018-02-28 16:48:24', '<b>Theming a child\'s birthday party is now a far easier task </b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">as the number of</span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Childrens-Party-Themes\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> themed birthday supplies available via the Internet</span></a> <i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">at very affordable prices</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is increasing all the time.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While some kids and their parents like to go for </span><b>popular TV and movie character themes</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, others often want to go for something a little more traditional,</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> like a pirate or unicorn party.</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> There are plenty of themed party supplies available for such parties too, </span><b>but what about activities that go with the birthday party theme?</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Here are just a few ideas centred around some of the most popular of today\'s </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Childrens-Party-Themes\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">kids birthday party themes</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: </span>\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pirate Party Ideas</span></h1>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-215\" src=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/pirate-birthday-party-for-boys_aeg8lq.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"399\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Long before Jack Sparrow hit the big screens children of all ages often begged Mum and Dad to </span><b>throw a pirate party for their birthday.</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> There are a number of </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Pirate-Treasure-Themed-Parties\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">different pirates themed party supply sets</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> available suitable for lots of different age groups </span><b>but to make your pirate party really go with a bang there have to be plenty of pirate related activities</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> going on at the party: </span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Walking the Plank </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All you need for this game is a </span><b>wooden plank set on the floor</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. For older kids, you can make the game </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">a little more challenging by setting the plank on bricks to raise it off the floor by a couple of inches. </span></i>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Each child has to </span><b>balance their way along the plank</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (harder than it sounds) without falling off into the sea. Real pirates used to blindfold their victims before sending them off the plank </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">so that too is a way to make the game even harder.</span></i>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Safer Sword Fighting </span></h2>\r\n<b>Pirates love sword fighting, kids love sword fighting</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> but even plastic swords can cause a little more damage than you’d like at a boisterous pirate party.</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> A safer alternative is to have the kids duel it out with balloon swords instead.</span></i>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Peg Leg Race </span></h2>\r\n<b>A three-legged race with a pirate twist</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The party guests are split into pairs and then each of them has one leg tied to their partner’s. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Set up an obstacle course in advance </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">(stuffed parrots, cardboard treasure chests, plastic palm trees, wherever your imagination takes you) and the </span><b>winners are the team who negotiate the course successfully with the fastest time.</b>\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Unicorn Party Ideas</span></h1>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-214\" src=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/unicorn-party.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"645\" height=\"427\" />\r\n\r\n<b>Unicorns have been popping up in fairy tales and other stories of enchanted worlds for centuries</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and unlike their close relatives dragons, they (usually) embody all that is sweet and good and therefore </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">appeal to kids of all ages, especially little girls.</span></i>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Unicorn-Themed-Parties\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">unicorn themed party</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> can be a great idea for children of all ages. Here are some ideas to make your unicorn party unique and unforgettable</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Unicorn Mane Races </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Print out </span><b>pictures of unicorns</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> from the internet or buy a few inexpensive unicorn posters. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Use ribbon or streamers to make enough ‘unicorn tails”</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> so that each guest has one of their own. </span><b>Choose an area (indoors or out) that has plenty of running space.</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Create a starting line and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">hang all the unicorn pictures a good running distance away.</span></i>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Divide the children into two equal teams. </span><b>Explain that the object is to be the first team to attach all of the colored streamers to its unicorn picture, forming the unicorn\'s rainbow mane.</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> The race is then run as a relay and play continues until one team has all of their streamers in place, forming a complete unicorn\'s mane.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fairy Story Time </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are so many great books that feature unicorns that not including a story time at your unicorn party would be a real shame. Some great titles to check out from the library? </span><b>The Unicorn and the Moon by Tomie DePaola, Unicorns I Have Known by Robert Vavra or If I Found a Wistful Unicorn: A Gift of Love by Ann Ashford.</b>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Unicorn Piñata </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Girls-Pinatas/Pinata-Unicorn\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">unicorn makes the perfect piñata</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Give each child a balloon sword to whack it with </span><b>for even more fun. </b>\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cowboy Party Ideas</span></h1>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-216\" src=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/DSC_0097-2-1024x681.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"568\" height=\"378\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kids have been having </span><b>cowboy themed birthday parties for decades</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> but they are still as popular as ever. You can certainly get a great many </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Search-Results?search_in_description=1&amp;keyword=cowboy&amp;inc_subcat=0&amp;sort=20a&amp;page=2\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">cool cowboy themed party supplies</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> but how about ideas for fun cowboy party activities’? </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Well here are just a few:</span></i>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gold Rush </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Scatter gold chocolate coins all around a designated area and </span><b>send the party guests off a gold “mining” expedition</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The kids, of course, get to keep whatever ‘gold” they find!</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Snakebite </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Before the party,</span><b> fill a plastic lidded tube with beans or something else that rattles</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Decorate the tube with eyes to make a “rattlesnake” Have your party guests sit in a circle and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">pass the \'rattler\'</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> while snippets of country and western music are played. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The player holding the rattler when the music stops (the one who \'bitten\') is out. </span><b>The last player left “unharmed” is the winner.</b>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Brand the Calf </span></h2>\r\n<b>Draw a picture of a calf or print one out from the Internet.</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Place the picture on a wall. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mark an X somewhere on the calf’s rear.</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Blindfold each child, spin him around, and then have him mark his brand (initials) on the calf with a crayon.</span><b> The child who comes closest to the X is the winner. </b>\r\n\r\n<i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some variations on this theme include pin the star on the sheriff and (of course) pin the tail on the horse.</span></i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Fun and Easy Game Ideas for Traditional Kids Birthday Party Themes', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'fun-easy-game-ideas-traditional-kids-birthday-party-themes', '', '', '2018-02-12 16:57:37', '2018-02-12 16:57:37', '', 0, 'https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/?p=213', 0, 'post', '', 0),
