an></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> available suitable for lots of different age groups </span><b>but to make your pirate party really go with a bang there have to be plenty of pirate related activities</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> going on at the party: </span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Walking the Plank </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All you need for this game is a </span><b>wooden plank set on the floor</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. For older kids, you can make the game </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">a little more challenging by setting the plank on bricks to raise it off the floor by a couple of inches. </span></i>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Each child has to </span><b>balance their way along the plank</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (harder than it sounds) without falling off into the sea. Real pirates used to blindfold their victims before sending them off the plank </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">so that too is a way to make the game even harder.</span></i>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Safer Sword Fighting </span></h2>\r\n<b>Pirates love sword fighting, kids love sword fighting</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> but even plastic swords can cause a little more damage than you’d like at a boisterous pirate party.</span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> A safer alternative is to have the kids duel it out with balloon swords instead.</span></i>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Peg Leg Race </span></h2>\r\n<b>A three-legged race with a pirate twist</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The party guests are split into pairs and then each of them has one leg tied to their partner’s. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Set up an obstacle course in advance </span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">(stuffed parrots, cardboard treasure chests, plastic palm trees, wherever your imagination takes you) and the </span><b>winners are the team who negotiate the course successfully with the fastest time.</b>\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Unicorn Party Ideas</span></h1>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-214\" src=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/unicorn-party.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"645\" height=\"427\" />\r\n\r\n<b>Unicorns have been popping up in fairy tales and other stories of enchanted worlds for centuries</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and unlike their close relatives dragons, they (usually) embody all that is sweet and good and therefore </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">appeal to kids of all ages, especially little girls.</span></i>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Unicorn-Themed-Parties\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">unicorn themed party</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> can be a great idea for children of all ages. Here are some ideas to make your unicorn party unique and unforgettable</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Unicorn Mane Races </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Print out </span><b>pictures of unicorns</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> from the internet or buy a few inexpensive unicorn posters. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Use ribbon or streamers to make enough ‘unicorn tails”</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> so that each guest has one of their own. </span><b>Choose an area (indoors or out) that has plenty of running space.</b>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Create a starting line and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">hang all the unicorn pictures a good running distance away.</span></i>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Divide the children into two equal teams. </span><b>Explain that the object is to be the first team to attach all of the colored streamers to its unicorn picture, forming the unicorn\'s rainbow mane.</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> The race is then run as a relay and play continues until one team has all of their streamers in place, forming a complete unicorn\'s mane.</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Fairy Story Time </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There are so many great books that feature unicorns that not including a story time at your unicorn party would be a real shame. Some great titles to check out from the library? </span><b>The Unicorn and the Moon by Tomie DePaola, Unicorns I Have Known by Robert Vavra or If I Found a Wistful Unicorn: A Gift of Love by Ann Ashford.</b>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Unicorn Piñata </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Girls-Pinatas/Pinata-Unicorn\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">unicorn makes the perfect piñata</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Give each child a balloon sword to whack it with </span><b>for even more fun. </b>\r\n<h1><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cowboy Party Ideas</span></h1>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter  wp-image-216\" src=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/DSC_0097-2-1024x681.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"568\" height=\"378\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Kids have been having </span><b>cowboy themed birthday parties for decades</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> but they are still as popular as ever. You can certainly get a great many </span><a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Search-Results?search_in_description=1&amp;keyword=cowboy&amp;inc_subcat=0&amp;sort=20a&amp;page=2\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">cool cowboy themed party supplies</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> but how about ideas for fun cowboy party activities’? </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Well here are just a few:</span></i>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Gold Rush </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Scatter gold chocolate coins all around a designated area and </span><b>send the party guests off a gold “mining” expedition</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. The kids, of course, get to keep whatever ‘gold” they find!</span>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Snakebite </span></h2>\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Before the party,</span><b> fill a plastic lidded tube with beans or something else that rattles</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. Decorate the tube with eyes to make a “rattlesnake” Have your party guests sit in a circle and </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">pass the \'rattler\'</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> while snippets of country and western music are played. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The player holding the rattler when the music stops (the one who \'bitten\') is out. </span><b>The last player left “unharmed” is the winner.</b>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Brand the Calf </span></h2>\r\n<b>Draw a picture of a calf or print one out from the Internet.</b><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Place the picture on a wall. </span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mark an X somewhere on the calf’s rear.</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Blindfold each child, spin him around, and then have him mark his brand (initials) on the calf with a crayon.</span><b> The child who comes closest to the X is the winner. </b>\r\n\r\n<i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Some variations on this theme include pin the star on the sheriff and (of course) pin the tail on the horse.</span></i>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Fun and Easy Game Ideas for Traditional Kids Birthday Party Themes', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '213-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-02-12 16:57:05', '2018-02-12 16:57:05', '', 213, 'https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/2018/02/12/213-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(219, 1, '2018-06-13 08:29:08', '2018-06-13 07:29:08', '<iframe width=\"644\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Y7TFlKgUndI\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; encrypted-media\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\r\n\r\n<h3>Video Transcription</h3>\r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> Right. Hello everybody. Welcome to the inaugural episode of the Go International Youtube series. I\'d like to welcome George SD Honest 00:09. Did I pronounce your last name correctly?\r\n \r\n<strong>George:</strong> Close enough, well done.\r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> Okay, awesome, perfect. So George let\'s begin by talking about yourself. Who are Go International and who is George and let\'s kick off from there.\r\n\r\n<strong>George:</strong> Okay let\'s do the short story otherwise we\'ll be here for about a week and you probably about crying. Go International really started about thirty years ago. It was a hobby more than anything else. Background I used to be a city broker. I got married and my wife decided that being a city broker at the time wasn\'t the lifestyle she wanted where I was disappearing for days on end or weeps at end 00:44 and so always had even kind of an entrepreneurial spirit. I knew I was unemployable, no one was ever going to employ me so I had to do something on my own. And it could have been really anything. I think the reason it became balloons is that in the States and the USA again about 26 27 years ago on the <a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/Balloons\">balloon</a> side of things and was a very interesting ad in a magazine called success magazine. And they worked sizing and talking balloon and all it was, was a piece of ribbon that went on the back of the balloon and it acted like a record. It had a very, they had lots of grooves in it. You\'re probably too young to remember records but they\'re things are go on the turntable and have little grooves in.\r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> Connected items that\'s what you refer to. \r\n\r\n<strong>George:</strong> And what you\'d use your thumbnail would become the needle, the grooves or his strip would be the record. And puts the balloon was around hollow resonating item not become 01:28 the speaker and so by sliding your thumbnail down the ribbon it would say things like happy birthday or congratulations. The product was actually crap but it was an introduction to booze and at that time when you\'re starting off in something you\'ll be a group really important on giving you feedback on what they think.\r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> And what year are we talking now more or less?\r\n\r\n<strong>George:</strong> Sorry?\r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> What year are we talking now?\r\n\r\n<strong>George:</strong> This was me ages.\r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> And this is still in the state or have you come back to the UK?\r\n\r\n<strong>George:</strong> I\'m back in the UK with his item now. And it was a case of, look, the company I spoke to them it was in those days they do have mobile phones. So you wouldn\'t remember that either and the mobile phones we did have with the size of a house break. And they were the kind of the confines of yuppie. So all we had was literally a telephone. I had a fax machine so it\'s really advanced in those days and this is how I would communicate with the states. You know email is nothing. It was just basically doing it that way. So I had to talk with the director, they were impressed with what we were saying or I was saying from the time and they invited me over to other lanta 02:27 where we kind of discuss what we can do with this product bringing to the UK. And then I came back in as I said in the beginning it\'s like you when you\'re new to this, you kind of listen to your peers. And my choice at that time were, i\'ve got an option of two items see up. Either going some mobile phones or you can go into balloons. Everyone told me don\'t go into mobile phones it\'s the Yuppie element. No one\'s gonna want them you\'re wasting your money. The company that I was going to work with on mobile phones actually sold to EE again quite a while ago from multi-millions, that\'s America. Because i\'ve got balloons and that\'s far more fun. So it shook her hand we did a deal we came back to the UK and we had this amazing little item and again, we couldn\'t promote it by the use of video, we couldn\'t do anything else other than go knocking on doors and try to introduce this product to anyone that we thought could be interested in balloons and going back to the 80s we didn\'t have the party shops that we have today. Balloons what you could walk high streets for hours and not find a balloon they were still very much the confines of fair grounds and then it kind of a circus isn\'t that kind of place that we didn\'t really have a good grounding you go after because the industry didn\'t exist and that\'s what made it tremendously exciting 03:36 exciting because I had carte blanche to 03:38 pretty much do things that no one else was doing because at the time they were probably in the UK five <a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk/EZ/Balloon-Wholesaler\">wholesalers of balloons</a> or balloon related products only five, fast forward to 2018 is probably a hundred and fifty-five trying to chase the same market. Yes we\'ve grown the industry but yeah we\'re now in a situation because of the success we created back then it really has become oversaturated. So came back to the UK into in 1980 whatever it was with this crappy piece of ribbon that pretty much gave them every penny I had to bring into the UK, it arrived by sea and kind of open these boxes and there I was you know boxes for the ribbons, a few balloons and no real market. So brought in the stands 04:18 from the UK who spent three months with us. And we\'re doing fun stuff like telemarketing which was never done in the UK at a time we\'re literally walking door-to-door knocking on doors.\r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> So you guys were doing knocking with because it blows my mind today with how you know I interact with us like okay buy something I go to Amazon or Ebay I go online, you know. Or I go into of course a shot from time to time but this Wow. So telesales and daughters or 04:44with the ribbon or with the other products also.\r\n\r\n<strong>George:</strong> It was attached to the balloon actually put at one for you i\'ve still got a few thousand in the warehouse but next time we talk i\'ll have some talking ribbons with me. They were so great we didn\'t sell out. But it was an introduction to market and as I said we were given carte blanche that we wanted there were no rules and so we try anything, we weren\'t scared of failing and the product really did need to be demoed. It was something that I had to put into your hands and to do it, to actually get the full benefit. So trying to do that with a leaflet drop or anything like that just wouldn\'t have worked.\r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> Gotcha.\r\n\r\n<strong>George:</strong> And from there we approached to manufacturers in the UK they were actually they\'re American but they had small bases in the UK. In fact one of the biggest ones operated from a garage in London back then that\'s how small the industry was and saying well you know this is who we are this is what we\'d like to do, would you consider talking to us? And the answer was no they closed with order. Who was this guy who knew absolutely nothing about the industry suddenly wanted to do all this stuff and so to increase our balloon product range every Friday, still Friday I used to grab a virgin airways flight from Heathrow Airport, fly across the USA and go to the wholesaler there and literally come back with probably 20 cases of balloons. \r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> You\'ve been on a journey, haven\'t you? Sorry to interrupt you, but this is incredible. I didn\'t, so because looking for the benefit of the people listening i\'ve known George for about six months and I got introduced to Go International as an e-commerce driven business because I knew that there was an online store and to hear this back story the idea of there being telesales, door-to-door, of the fire, this is incredible I\'m just blown away keep, sort of keep going. So we\'re on the you\'re on a virgin flight, I think well you\'re headed off to the States anyway.\r\n\r\n<strong>George:</strong> Absolutely, and so yeah we were going back with I think at the very peak we were coming back with I would stay 30 cases of balloons on the Monday morning flight and I needed three Porter\'s to get them off the off the plane and to carry them through customs for us.\r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> It sounds own being in India dude.\r\n\r\n<strong>George:</strong> We had such a great villa, that was just me and I had such a great relationship with Virgin Atlantic that the deal was that if I did their parties for them free of charge then let me take all this stuff free of charge. So yeah we had porters carrying through and people like looking at me thinking what the hell\'s this guy got in these boxes. But it was great because yeah we did the New Year\'s party for verging back there I got to meet Richard Branson.\r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> Wow, we need to come back to that bit of course that\'s going to be interesting to any. We\'ll do an episode just on meet Richard Branson because people gonna find that curious. \r\n\r\n<strong>George:</strong> [inaudible 07:23 to 07:28] couple of photos. But yes this went on for about three or four months and then the main manufacturers you had divisions in the UK but kind of getting a little jittery they were saying you know this guy\'s come along all of a sudden we can see all this product in the marketplace, what\'s he doing. Is he just dumping it what\'s he doing. But we were really building relationships and it\'s something that i\'ve always loved I love to kind of go into something that\'s relatively new and show them ways of kind of increasing what they\'re doing.\r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> And you showed that\'s getting a little bit lost today with how consumers are. I feel that like it\'s, I mean, you know I mean I come in kind of as a little bit of a layperson so one of the things I often think about is that I for example don\'t have any particular brand allegiance with Amazon, I go there because it\'s convenient but it\'s not about brand loyalty. It could be Amazon or ebay interchangeably and it sounds like the way that you operating then perhaps and I don\'t know if it\'s a challenge and we\'ll come and talk about that you know down the line in the kind of balloon and party marketplace today but certainly you talked about that one relationships. And I always think that you know it\'s not something that I have with Amazon and ebay and it sounds like something that\'s quite important to the growth in the history of well, George as well as go international and kind of your path.\r\n\r\n<strong>George:</strong> If we\'re setting on website so we do what we do then it just becomes a price consideration. You suddenly come a pretty picture with the price lets as far as it goes. I still believe that the party industry is a specialist industry. I think that relationships are key to that. I loved in the beginning because I knew my accounts one-to-one I could pick up a phone speak from I saw them all. Now with over 16,000 accounts it\'s pretty difficult to call in and know them all personally. We used to do exhibitions we don\'t even bother with the exhibitions anymore because again it just becomes a very very expensive and shaking exercise. So from our perspective the ones that we really do the best with are the ones that know me and know my philosophy and understand that what I\'m trying to do. And it\'s also not about selling product, it\'s about how in the month 09:31 stand that they\'re not just buying the product on the wholesale basis, we\'re actually showing them what to do with our products.\r\n\r\n<strong>Deepak:</strong> Okay. And with I mean that would probably present quite a significant challenge with the because you were saying for example that you know there\'s over 5,000 accounts where I think you said 16 maybe. Yeah, okay. So how because I assume that your competitors as well as your accounts as well as everybody in the marketplace for example probably has the same issue. And I just wonder like do you have any, for example practical things that you still do that you find you know kind of make the difference. Or do you have any advice for someone who says well George it\'s very difficult for me to compete against town land 10:15 because you know Mary is just going off to buy a couple of things for her Christmas preparations. What would your advice be to someone who has that challenge?\r\n\r\n<strong>George:</strong> I think understand the market more than anything else. I the problem with the balloon industry it\'s so easy to get involved with. You literally you buy a packet of balloons off ebay if you want to you buy a cylinder of gas from ebay if you want to or Amazon. And all of a sudden you\'re a balloon decorator, you know you\'ve got the balloons you see you this is another problem the industry, it\'s very easy for people to look at how to do without really understanding what\'s really behind it. And for someone that spent their life trying to educate people and help people understand what the industry is really about, to see my customers being undercut because all the sudden Amazon ebay are literally dumping product on the market 20 News got a five-pound note in their pocket it makes it more challenging for them. Well I score exceedingly high points is where I\'m allowed to work with them, you know two years ago I was made chairman of an association called NOBAS, that\'s the National Association of balloon artists and suppliers. Through the education we provide there and through the interaction they have not directly with me 