wnie points. Why does everyone go self-employed, why does everyone want to be their own boss? The two words always come to mind when you want to do this is freedom, and money. How\'s that working a helpful with you cut a path going different directions all of a sudden your freedoms gone, you\'re working more as than you ever have before, you\'re the bottle washing, you\'re the toilet cleaner, you\'re everything you\'re meant to be. When it comes to money, most people it\'s industry actually take a dip in money when it comes to starting a business in it and initially, the dropout rate is in ease of 92 percent in the first year because it\'s so easy to get involved with. They see the great stuff being done, they see the huge corporations doing tremendously well and they want a chunk for that, but they don\'t realize that there\'s a lot of work involved as well, so going self-employed and going into the party industry we\'ve got a number of people at the point you in their directions been tremendously well but we get to be the vast majority are still dabbling and it because a double as market. as we said you buy a few balloons, you buy a bottle of gas, all of a sudden your balloon decorators, you do your friends, you do your relatives weddings or whatever for them and then all the sudden you realize that what do I do next, where does the marketing come into it, how do I promote my business. Then that\'s always been our strength, we always look at the marketing of your business, we always try and help our customers look at what\'s next, rather than just kind of say well here\'s your product see you later goodbye now and that\'s why we have continued to grow of course we don\'t win them all or always people out there shopping on price and nothing but price. and we gradually in most of the cases they are the ones that are part of that nineteen ninety five percent that fail in the first year. because any business you\'re going to it\'s not purely balloons, it has changed, 