(248, 1, '2018-07-11 09:00:51', '2018-07-11 08:00:51', '<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ryHNWKKWTWE\" width=\"643\" height=\"400\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\nHi guys! Welcome back to Episode 7, of a journey with Go International,  George hello good afternoon how are you buddy?\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\nIs this now month 2, we\'re done seven?\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\nWe’ve done seven, so one a week.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\nIt seems like only yesterday.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\nThat\'s true so 7 and we still got a combined total about 300 views. So, thank you for those 300 views.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\nThank you for today.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\nThank you, George, I want to talk to you I want to ask you rather about someone who\'s getting into the balloon industry for the first time, talk me through the first 90 days of, “Hey I’ve decided I want to get into the balloon industry you know, WTF do I do?\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\nI think, the the very first question you ask yourself is why do you want to do it, is there a reason you\'ve chosen this industry, have you seen something that inspired you, are you looking to do it part-time is this something that you can see yourself growing in, what areas are interests in, are you are you that, there are so many different areas are you interested in becoming a vendor, where you\'re walking around markets with hands full of foil balloons to sell to the children are you looking to integrate it into an existing business, I do have a gift shop card shop in the thinking division of foil balloons.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\nLet\'s make it a little bit more practical, so we\'ve got a reference point then perhaps. Let\'s say that I am a mother of two, I am a family woman, I\'ve worked in...\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\nI’d shave if I were you.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\nLooks good you should meet some of my actual aunties. I\'ve worked in the gift card industry for the last 10 to 15 years and the part of it that I particularly, enjoyed was the stuff related to the parties; birthday cards,  some of the decorations and I\'ve got a little bit of money saved, maybe I\'ve got 20,000 pounds saved and I\'d like to give it a go with my husband\'s support getting into or maybe starting, my own shop focusing on balloons. So let\'s take that as an example because I want it to be a little bit of a lifestyle business doing something that I enjoy but making enough money to you know pay for my bills support my two kids what what what did the first 90 days of that situation look like.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\nOkay, I would again go back to the why it\'s tremendously important that that\'s we do are why as we also do our calculations. Do we need a shop from day one? I would say absolutely in this industry no the failure rate within the balloon industry is a staggering 80% within the first year. The reason for that and that\'s higher than industry averages, industry averages are probably half businesses go within five years but with the balloon industry because it is so easy to get into on a whim you buy a bottle of gas, you buy a bag of balloons, you you decorate a few friends venues and all of a sudden you\'re in the industry. The reality sets in when you\'re sitting at home with your two children and your husband he\'s saying how much we made today and you\'re saying the phone hasn\'t ring and nothing\'s happened and then you look at it why isn\'t it happening. So it is with any business not just with the balloon industry it really is a case of perfect planning before you start whispering it\'s possibly can be. Write down what are your overheads are going to be write down what you expect your breakeven to be write down that you understand for the first 16 months to a year if not more, for that it\'s the break-even to loss scenario who are your customer bases going to be it really is, so important that before even stepping into my domain about you know coming in to me and saying I want to buy so that knowing why you want to do it, I mean why is a huge question that very few of us ask especially in something that\'s so easy to get involved with it can but regrettably as I said the reason the fallout rate is so high, is when they bought their bottle of gas in their balloons and the accessories that go with it and we\'re a tremendous guilty company of underselling you know if the fictional lady comes in to us and wants to spend her 20 odd.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\nLet’s call her Joanne.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\nHuh she\'s a nice girl a little naive maybe if you can spend that much money on day one and a husband nice little chat with her too. It’s, we always undersell, we don\'t want to sell you absolutely everything from day one ie the electronic air inflate, as a split-second sizes which doing wonderful things with balloons make your life easier. We want you to do you were apprenticeship we want you to undergo a training regime, where from day one you know what you need to do and more importantly you know how to market yourself.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\nOkay.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\nIt\'s something that we find the biggest reason for failure in this industry is because there isn\'t enough customers it\'s because they don\'t have enough confidence in what they\'re going to do with this is, purely an idea and the idea sometimes grows but mainly doesn\'t.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\nOkay.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\nSounds a bit depressing, but you know the reality is I wouldn\'t want anyone to get coming to this industry and fail, I hate seeing anyone fail in this because I know the potential is amazing and now that we have customers that started from zilch they\'re doing tremendously well but I\'ve seen so many fall by the wayside because they haven\'t had that good plan of action and I said it does sound a bit kind of doom and gloomy but I don\'t want anyone to waste their time more importantly for the existing