nces. So is the big one in Warwick is it in Barcelona or is it in San Diego or is it are they a little bit different?\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nWell WBC is by far the largest it doesn\'t get the American market is still the largest market in the world, they travel in from all over the USA to San Diego there\'s a lot of Europeans going across there such as Europeans from from all over the world, now they congregate and I don’t know exactly I don\'t know what the exact numbers are perhaps I can look it up let you know next time but there\'s a good few hundred turn up.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nOkay, no, amazing, it\'s fascinating, alright. So we\'ve got one or two more minutes before we wrap up today so what I\'d love to ask then is, what is the within the balloon industry what is the, which kind of business is the one that you\'re most often saying is it the is it is it the kind of mom-and-pop store that\'s a local one, is that the young strappy guy who wants to start an ecommerce business, is it someone who wants to do specific wedding based events therefore they they\'re mobile, which is it you\'re seeing the most of at the moment?\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nYes, all of those.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nOkay.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nWhat you choose yeah there are some giant giants out there we regrettably it as we\'ve said before it\'s become very competitive and some of the manufacturers that swore, blind they would always support us and work with us have now leaped from the wholesaler and gone direct to the retailer some of taken a step further and leaped over the wholesaler and the retailer and gone direct to the end-user as well.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nOk.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nAnd there are some real huge operations out there and now there are web-based businesses that they take a great deal of cash off the table for the standard mom-and-pop type operations and that\'s where they\'re h2h the p2p they get a person-to-person, human to human relationship comes into effect, you\'ve got to stand up and you\'ve got to be seen and you\'ve got to be heard, they\'ve got to know exactly what, you\'re capable of doing you\'ve got to build those relationships. If you don\'t have the infrastructure or the ability to have these huge infrastructures have been created by the manufacturers, you can\'t possibly compete with them you don\'t even try and compete you sell on your own terms you become an expert in your own right you become a specialist in your own right and you have the confidence to sell in your own right.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nRight dude it makes complete sense I mean I\'m in my own way, I\'m experiencing the same when i\'ve gone into an industry that\'s you know SEO driven and there\'s bigger better funded companies and you think well how can I build my own name and it sounds very similar in many respects and perhaps that\'s just something across business in use in general perfect, okay George thank you this is episode 7 next week it\'s a two-month mark buddy excited.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nWeek eight?\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nYeah it\'ll be week eight. I\'m surprised as well genuinely, I didn\'t think that we\'d know I thought that we\'d make a week eight but I was surprised it\'s happened. Has it really been two months since we did the first one?\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nYeah I didn’t really know what\'s gonna stick with you too much to be honest.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nI was like yes Deepak keep getting your hooks in. Perfect, all right George thank you so much I’ll talk to ya next week buddy.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nGreat weekend bye', 'A Journey With Go International | George Oustayiannis | Episode 7', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '248-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-07-09 13:30:36', '2018-07-09 12:30:36', '', 248, 'https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/248-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
