t video is the right way for for many people to go because, it could be a great message, it could be a fantastic message but it gets lost amongst the noise and this is what worries me with all the social media channels at the moment, Facebook was tremendously good for us a few years ago when it came to advertising promotion but again we\'ve gone down a route where you\'re getting lost amongst all the noise how many notifications am I getting a day now from Facebook that really don\'t interest me and you have to keep switching them off and sometimes the good messages get lost as well. So I think from my perspective we\'re we\'re kind of doing a scattergun approach where we\'re doing a little bit of everything I\'m seeing what works for us it\'s never going to be a case of one size fitting all yeah big video may be tremendous, it may be work we are getting some nice views on various things we are doing which is great more thumbs-up and thumbs-down which is encouraging to, know who do thumbs down actually something around special windows but it\'s a case of trying these things and seeing you know what works for me to be honest with you.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nOkay, no absolutely it completely makes sense and what I mean, would you then for example as you know we\'re undertaking you would you advocate for someone else you know try a little bit of everything and see what works or no give give give give video give give Instagram three months your combined efforts and scrap everything else and let\'s really try and focus on this one thing because of the payoff, what\'s your answer to a question like that that you know also comes relates to the wider business, in general doesn\'t it I presume in lots of different ways.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nAbsolutely, I think in our industry most of our business owners tend to be independent. So it\'s maybe one or two people working within the business, so to suddenly hit them with all these things they need to do can be mind-blowing without even looking at you\'re just doing that daily kind of wake up and do your stuff. So I think I would recommend that they specialize on something their mission and that they\'re comfortable with and they know about you it could be Facebook, Facebook could work tremendously well for them I know it\'s a platform that many of our customers are using and very very happy with, it maybe video because they\'re comfortable in front of the camera they feel they can attract an audience and get views and lights or whatever they\'re actually trying to achieve and also because our products are very visual, then it has to be something with imagery there it\'s Instagram whether it is snapchat with this video whether it\'s it\'s Facebook it\'s got to be something where they are comfortable that they\'re actually showing something that people are going to be interested in, there\'s nothing worse than disheartening them than you have spending 15 minutes to a half an hour on this and then finding else finding out noone not actually seeing it. So you know and again I again that we went back a few months ago, it\'s not going to happen overnight you know don\'t be disheartened when you’ve 11 or 12 as we have and no one looks at them, because it\'ll happen with time but there are only so many hours in the day which ones who actually go for. I would still say based on the feedback I get, from our customers looking at what they\'re currently doing, so many are very uncomfortable with doing this so me a very a couple of second video in front of ourselves and doing this from our customer\'s perspective, but they feel more comfortable playing with the Facebook element still and I would recommend playing with Facebook but mastering Facebook as well because, so many is still not doing it right.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nOkay, okay no that makes a lot of sense. So is it a balance in between you know working in areas that you\'re comfortable in and and beginning there as a point of focus?\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nI\'m a great fan of being out of your comfort zone there\'s nothing better than pushing yourself and as you know I always do things that it could be a little bit scary I guess. But initially it is really getting into the habit of doing stuff and making it part of your weekly routine, if you\'re going to do three Facebook posts a week make sure you do three Facebook posts a week. Make sure you delegate the time to it and it becomes habit, even with these you know that time - it\'s like I\'m busy I don\'t do it but you made me do it so here I am so you do need to dedicate that time and take it very very seriously, you know we have a lot of fun we have a lot between ourselves but the serious aspect of this the reason we are doing it more than anything else is for us to get exposure. I think from my perspective it\'s honestly to get people to believe and this this is concernedly crazy but I honestly believe in in the world my own if people actually get to know who they\'re dealing with, rather than just this pretty picture on a price. I think that actually going to cover a track to a small because I think maybe: A) They\'re gonna realize there\'s an area of expertise here that I\'ve got to offer it\'s not just a case of “Hi let\'s have a chat” over a 30 year period of doing what I\'ve been doing there\'s an area of expertise which I would like to kind of pass on to our customers and more important as I said it does give you a kind of wider bandwidth of who you are what you\'re doing.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nIt makes complete sense and I think that element the personalization is really important because there\'s a always going to be especially from you know the discussions that we\'ve had one of the interesting things that you\'ve always told me about is you know we\'ve got an area of expertise that you know a high street stores such as you know, let\'s just say the Poundlands of course they cannot match because you know they have an extremely generalist approach and for me for those customers that do care about you know the personal side to it these videos give them the opportunity to be like oh ok so, this is you know this is the man the, person, the company this is part of the team buying from and for some of them is going to help build that loyalty. So then should we as business owners in the balloon industry should we ignore what our competitors are doing then? Because you know there\'s some competitors you know we\'ve made reference to historically that you know are doing tons maybe whether it be on Youtube or doing tons on so do we ignore that, do we what\'s your response to someone who will say George you\'re right I\'m doing the Facebook stuff and I enjoy doing it but these guys seem to be doing tons on video should I do video then or should I not worry I\'ll be ignoring the elephant in the room or what\'s your opinion on that.?\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nI think with competitors we\'ve said this again before our worst competitors ourselves, so course you need to know what the competitors is doing it\'s tremendously important that you understand what\'s going on in your industry, whether they\'re true competitors are just people making a mess it\'s a different conversation but look within stop looking without focus on what you do well and make that be your unique selling proposition don\'t try and copy what the house is doing. There are people coming to Facebook for the very first time and within a matter of weeks they\'re great they\'re getting a huge following because they\'re giving something that the general public one but their consumer wants, and that\'s the important thing not necessarily doing what you want to do because as we said before this is something I want to do, but doing something we believe our customers, our clients want to know about and want to see. So yes competitors are important you know we can\'t ignore them they do things that sometimes are good that we can obviously learn from as well, but focus on yourself more than anything else and bring something to market which is you.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nAbsolutely, absolutely it makes complete sense and an element of uniqueness I think, is you know can be captured by video in a way that other areas can\'t. So let\'s then talk about your your your first experience of a video that relatively speaking has gone viral compared to the other videos right I mean we\'re getting a hundred views or less on these videos that\'s the only odd certainly on on youtube because it sounds it seems like nobody\'s really that familiar with with Go on Youtube, but certainly on Facebook, I feel like it\'s been quite different and each of the videos get a lot more views comparatively on Facebook than they do on Youtube. However, with all of that being said, I know you made a video that\'s got already a couple of hundred views, maybe up to 500 now can you talk me through a little bit about what the videos about what you think that you did differently that means that that has got ten times more views in these videos.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nAgain it\'s basing on what we believed our clients and customers needed to see there\'s a new product that\'s come to market in this case it was called an Aqua Balloon. There was a lot of hype and misconception of what it actually was, so a very quick three-minute video where apparently, I fluffed tying it at the end, tying a balloon at the end which everyone loves, It was something that really hit with what people want you to know about this product, very basic. It was very quick sharing of the product and what it does, what it is, and me fluff tying at the end of it which, we kept it in on purpose because as I said before don\'t be afraid of making mistakes, mistakes are good.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nYeah.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nAnd we learn from mistakes and so many people are afraid of this year, so god it\'s not perfect it\'s not perfect and I shouldn\'t do it. The whole point is it\'s never going to be perfect, there\'s no such thing as perfection. So leave it in there if you make a mistake it becomes a talking point, which it has that\'s great.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nWell buddy, I\'m really pleased that you\'ve got video that\'s got a couple of hundred views and you know keep doing.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nAlmost five.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nAbsolutely, so that that could be the first video to clear five figures in time and see see where it goes and that will be an achievement and that video is gonna be around forever. So, fantastic! Another important question I\'ve got, you know when a business goes through periods of turbulence, for example you hit a month and kind of sales are down or you know, how should a business owner cope or what should they do in moments where, you know for example one of the things that we discussed with a nature of an ecommerce business, there are many, many, many different potential factors for why sales could could be down. What\'s your what\'s your advice when the answer doesn\'t seem that obvious or you know you\'ve a team and everyone\'s a bit miffed as to why that there\'s no direct you know cause what do you do in those circumstances?\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nI think one week or one month or a quarter doesn\'t represent where you\'re going or where you\'ve been, you obviously have to look at your things is tremendously important but you are not going to know just by having a quick snapshot and looking at at something and wondering why you\'ve really again got to understand, why your figures are what they are I have you stopped offering what people are looking for are you no longer offering a price break that makes sense in what you\'re doing, are you losing customers because there\'s an element of your business, it could be website down, it could be that you and something\'s happened that you are aware of. So you\'re obviously looking all the time to find out where you can kind of stop these gaps and and kind of plug the holes but you can\'t really judge a business in a week or a month and our sales figures, we\'ve said before from the Go perspective, I think for the month of March were probably gonna see another you know double 25% increase at Go, which is great but again I\'m always looking at why as well you know, why is it up no one\'s looking weights down but why are we up and how can we maintain that? It\'s a very difficult thing to do because in especially in this day and age do I thank you and say great because we\'ve done a video now and 4 to 500 other additional people have seen my face I think this guy\'s great, when it goes next down next month I say it\'s because they\'ve seen the videos and they don\'t like my face so it\'s gone. So yeah we\'re doing this thing where we\'re trying a little bit of everything and yes figures are important and if we\'re not making a profit tha we shouldn\'t be doing this anyway but again you\'ve got it you\'ve got to have you\'ve got to have set targets where you\'re looking at what you\'re looking, at when you\'re looking at it and then trying to analyze from there.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nOkay, okay no that makes a lot of sense and I think that a lot of time certainly you know in my experience as well when when when things take a sudden bad turn the knee-jerk response is to be like war you know WTF has happened, sack everyone of course and it\'s a completely human response and I know that you know there\'s been moments where you\'ve kept me up at night because you’re like, “Deepak, this has happened,” and I\'m on a bus because I\'m drinking on the way out and I\'m like I sent George and even had a 3 am what am I doing? I shouldn’t do stuff like that.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nAnd I reply at 3:30.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nYeah, absolutely, which is both good and bad so we\'re both tearing our hair out. Okay fantastic, George, that makes complete sense. So in this final and two minutes that we\'ve got, what you know for for this coming year with kind of all of the the new activity that there is an outside of Facebook right, if there\'s one new activity that you think in light of what you\'ve seen that you know someone in the balloon industry could do what would it be, whether that\'s a particular kind of video, whether that\'s information about a balloon whether that\'s an operational change could you talk to me about one new learning that you have implemented or seen yourself that has helped your business in 2018?\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nOkay I think again because I\'m old school it\'s not necessarily a new learning, it\'s more revisiting the old stuff as well and revisiting your old accounts and seeing, who they are it\'s so much easier to bring an old account back, rather than trying to regenerate new all the time and it\'s so much easier to work with your existing accounts and see if there\'s additional services you come up with them as well.  We\'ve got a new product we\'re launching this week which again it’s exclusive for the UK, it\'s because of talking to customers and saying; well what\'s missing, what you need, what should we be bringing? So again it\'s down to old school and the old school is talking to people and suddenly you\'re afraid of doing that right now we are depending on this kind of stuff to stop us having to actually make that call pick up the phone, go downstairs and shake someone\'s hand and we\'ve got to do that it\'s so insane so essentially people actually know who we are.\r\n\r\n<b>Deepak:</b>\r\n\r\nI think it\'s an incredibly important because there\'s also the wave of people that want to do all of the kind of tech-gizmo type stuff but it\'s like, when did you actually call like some of the people that you\'ve done business with historically and it\'s the numbers will probably be frightening low for a lot of people like what do you mean actually pick up the phone and give them a ring just say hello it\'s like, well yeah no so yeah it makes a lot of sense. Okay George thank you for your time and as ever and everybody let\'s see if we can get this video past 100 leads in the first couple of days at least Ii\'ll have something to say to George see you guys.\r\n\r\n<b>George:</b>\r\n\r\nThank you bye bye.', 'Picking Your Social Media Platform | Go International | Episode 11', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'picking-social-media-platform-gointernational-episode-11', '', '', '2018-08-29 16:56:24', '2018-08-29 15:56:24', '', 0, 'https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/?p=261', 0, 'post', '', 0),
