(272, 1, '2018-09-10 16:50:05', '2018-09-10 15:50:05', 'You\'ve been online and chosen the <a href=\"https://www.gointernational.co.uk\">kid\'s party supplies</a> that are perfect for your child\'s big bash. You\'ve planned the games, shopped for the food and even taken the time to order some great children\'s party favours as well. There\'s just one thing left; what are they all going to drink.\r\n\r\nHeading to the supermarket and filling a trolley full of cans or bottles of pop can get super expensive very quickly (so blowing all that cash you saved on buying kid\'s party supplies online right there) A great alternative? A tasty kids punch. Everyone will remain \'properly hydrated\' and, if you try your hand at one of these fun recipes they are likely to be entertained and/or amused as well.\r\n<h3>Harry Potter\'s Butterbeer</h3>\r\nHave some Harry Potter fans on the party guest list? Then they\'ll love this punch that was inspired by the very beverage that Harry and Co loved to sip on their big trips to Hogsmeade.\r\n\r\nWhat You’ll Need\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>1 cup light or dark brown sugar</li>\r\n 	<li>2 tablespoons water</li>\r\n 	<li>6 tablespoon butter</li>\r\n 	<li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>\r\n 	<li>1/2 teaspoon cider vinegar</li>\r\n 	<li>1/2 pint heavy cream</li>\r\n 	<li>1/2 teaspoon rum extract (which is not alcoholic!)</li>\r\n 	<li>Four 12-ounce bottles of cream soda</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHow to Make Harry Potter’s Butterbeer\r\n\r\nBrown Sugar Syrup\r\n\r\nIn a small saucepan over a medium heat, combine the brown sugar and water. Bring to a gentle boil and cook, stirring often, until the mixture reads 240 degrees on a candy thermometer.\r\n\r\nStir in the butter, salt, vinegar and 1/4 of the heavy cream.\r\n\r\nSet aside to cool to room temperature.\r\n\r\nOnce the mixture has cooled, stir in the rum extract.\r\n\r\nWhipped Topping:\r\n\r\nIn a medium bowl, combine 2 tablespoons of the brown sugar mixture and the remaining 1/2 cup of heavy cream. Use an electric mixer to beat until just thickened, but not completely whipped, about 2 to 3 minutes.\r\n\r\nTo serve, scoop a tablespoon of Brown Sugar Syrup into each glass and then each glass nearly to the top with cream soda, before spooning the whipped topping over each.\r\n<h3>Hulk Punch</h3>\r\nOkay, so he isn\'t the happiest of The Avengers but he is a pretty cool character that kids love. And they will love this Hulk inspired green punch as well. To make it even better, when shopping for kids party supplies look out for Hulk or Avengers themed cups to serve this punch in. They are pretty easy to find.\r\n\r\nWhat You\'ll Need\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Sprite</li>\r\n 	<li>1-2 Fresh Limes, Sliced</li>\r\n 	<li>Yellow Food Coloring</li>\r\n 	<li>Green Food Coloring</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHow to Make Hulk Punch\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>In a pitcher combine Sprite,  and 2 drops of food yellow and green food coloring.</li>\r\n 	<li>Stir well.</li>\r\n 	<li>Slice fresh limes into halves and place into the mixture.</li>\r\n 	<li>Refrigerate punch for at least 2 hours before serving.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Sparkling Princess Punch</h3>\r\nThis pretty purple punch looks just like a grown up\'s drink (perfect for little princesses) just minus the alcohol.\r\n\r\nWhat You\'ll Need\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>1 tin (400g) pineapple</li>\r\n 	<li>1-2 packs frozen raspberries</li>\r\n 	<li>1 litre apple or cherry juice</li>\r\n 	<li>1.5 litre sparkling water</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>How to Make Sparkling Princess Punch</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Cut the pineapple slices into small pieces and put into a big bowl</li>\r\n 	<li>Pour in pineapple juice.</li>\r\n 	<li>Add the frozen raspberries.</li>\r\n 	<li>Pour in apple or cherry juice</li>\r\n 	<li>Add sparkling water</li>\r\n 	<li>Chill before serving</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Perfect Party Punches for Kids', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'perfect-party-punches-for-kids', '', '', '2018-08-29 16:58:42', '2018-08-29 15:58:42', '', 0, 'https://www.gointernational.co.uk/blog/?p=272', 0, 'post', '', 0),
